    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I also just answered on SO, but the solution is rather simple: when doing a `groupby().last()`, the last item for each column will be calculated. So, you can just reset the index level to make a column of it, and then do the groupby:\n\n```\nIn [44]: df.reset_index(level='Date').groupby(level=0).last()\nOut[44]:\nColumnName  Date  Value\nName\nA              3      6\nB              4      6\n```\n"
  },
